{
  "doc_id": "6613",
  "text": "Due to its simplicity, the index of Tibaldi and Molteni (henceforth denoted as TM-Index) [CITATION_1] , which is based on the original idea of Lejenäs and Økland [CITATION_2] , has become a standard in automated blocking detection analyses. An important problem of the TM-Index is that it cannot effectively distinguish between blocking and cut-off low patterns, since both fulfill the TM-Index criteria. The modified TM-Index MTM [CITATION_3] has a higher rejection rate for cut-off lows. Restrictions in the Rex criteria can be considered as implementations of independent filters which show synergetic effects if they are used in succession. The zonal TM-Index has been extended to latitudes by Scherrer et al. [CITATION_4] .",
